title: Televerket (Sweden) - Wikipedia
snippet: Televerket was a Swedish State authority acting as a state-owned corporation (public enterprise), responsible for telecommunications in Sweden from 1853 until 1993. Originally it was named Kongl. Elektriska Telegraf-Werket (literally: Royal Electric Telegraph Agency), which was founded in 1853.

title: About: Televerket (Sweden)
snippet: Elektriska Telegraf-Werket (literally: Royal Electric Telegraph Agency), which was founded in 1853. Its name changed to Kongl. Telegrafverket in 1871, Kungl. Telegrafverket in 1903, the prefix Kungl. (English: Royal) was dropped in 1946 and the name was further modernised to Televerket in 1953.

title: The Swedish Newspaper of America
snippet: The Swedish end was Kongl. Telegrafverket (founded in 1853 as Konglige Elektriska Telegraf-Werket - literally: Royal Electric Telegraph Agency), later changed to Kungl. Telegrafverket in 1903. The Kungliga (Royal) was dropped in 1946 and the name was further modernized to Televerket in 1953.

title: Telegrafverket, Televerket, TeliaSonera, Telia :: organisation
snippet: År 1925 fick Telia det tekniska ansvaret för landets rundradioverksamhet och 1956 också för televisionssändningarna. År 1953 antogs namnet Televerket och 1993 antogs Telia då en ny svensk telelag avskaffade Telias faktiska om än ej formella monopolställning.
